; Slice β (2026-04-24) — Study zone primitive scaffold. Three shelf-wall
; Box primitives give the researcher a visual landmark so Kant's time in
; the Study is visible from a top-down camera. Sized to roughly mark the
; zone's footprint; the Blender-authored .glb eventually replaces this
; build (tracked under the backlog in the Slice β plan).
;
; Scene root sits at (-33.33, 0, -33.33) to match
; ``src/erre_sandbox/world/zones.py`` ``ZONE_CENTERS[STUDY]``
; (``-WORLD_SIZE_M / 3``). Keep that transform in sync whenever
; ``WORLD_SIZE_M`` changes; the wireframe in ``BoundaryLayer.gd``
; ``zone_rects`` is the parallel mirror.

